From: Vasily Gorbik <gor@linux.ibm.com>
Subject: s390/barrier: Make array_index_mask_nospec() __always_inline
Patch-mainline: v7.0-rc6
Git-commit: c5c0a268b38adffbb2e70e6957017537ff54c157
References: bsc#1263068

Description:   s390: nospec hardening for entry code
Symptom:       None visible. Missing nospec hardening in s390 entry
Problem:       The syscall number could reach the dispatch table without a
               nospec array bound, r12 was not scrubbed on all kernel entry
               paths after earlier entry changes, and the s390-specific
               array_index_mask_nospec() helper was not forced to inline.
Solution:      Add array_index_nospec() before syscall table lookup, clear r12
               in the affected entry handlers, and mark
               array_index_mask_nospec() as __always_inline so the masking
Reproduction:  -

Upstream-Description:

              s390/barrier: Make array_index_mask_nospec() __always_inline

              Mark array_index_mask_nospec() as __always_inline to guarantee the
              mitigation is emitted inline regardless of compiler inlining decisions.

              Fixes: e2dd833389cc ("s390: add optimized array_index_mask_nospec")
              Cc: stable@kernel.org
              Reviewed-by: Ilya Leoshkevich <iii@linux.ibm.com>
              Signed-off-by: Vasily Gorbik <gor@linux.ibm.com>


Signed-off-by: Vasily Gorbik <gor@linux.ibm.com>
Acked-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
---
 arch/s390/include/asm/barrier.h |    4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/arch/s390/include/asm/barrier.h
+++ b/arch/s390/include/asm/barrier.h
@@ -60,8 +60,8 @@ do {									\
  * @size: number of elements in array
  */
 #define array_index_mask_nospec array_index_mask_nospec
-static inline unsigned long array_index_mask_nospec(unsigned long index,
-						    unsigned long size)
+static __always_inline unsigned long array_index_mask_nospec(unsigned long index,
+							     unsigned long size)
 {
 	unsigned long mask;
 
